perform the following tasks related to ./agent.py, do not perform tasks are that completed, after a task is completed, in ./init.prompt, change task to "task (completed)"

task.init_spec (completed) {
  implement the logic according to spec below:
  spec {
    local_llm {
      host: localhost
      port: 11434
      model: qwen3-coder:30b-determin
    }
    input_prompt:the first argument
    cli_find_skill_markdowns: find ./skills/ -type f -name "SKILL.md"
    skill_file_paths:run cli command {cli_find_skill_markdowns}
    intent_prompt {
      skill_file_paths {
        {skill_file_paths}
      }
      instruction {
        {input_prompt}
      }
      action {
        return the file paths in skill_file_paths that maps the intent of instruction, one path per line, no explanation, no extra words
      } 
    }
    print "loading skills...\n"
    related_skill_file_paths:send {intent_prompt} to local_llm
    final_prompt:"contex {"
    for each {file_path} in related_skill_file_paths {
      skill_file_content: get file content from {file_path}
      tmp: remove the ending "/SKILL.md" from {file_path}
      tmp: remove the beginning "./" from {tmp}
      python_import_package: replace all "/" with "." in {tmp}
      final_prompt .= {skill_file_content} . "\nREMEMBER: from {python_import_package} import SKILL\n"
    }
    final_prompt .= "}\n"
    final_prompt .= task {
      {input_prompt}
    }
    final_prompt .= action {
      learn from context, use context as example, generate python code to complete the task, show me the python code only, no explanation, no extra words
    }
    result:send {final_prompt} to local_llm with streaming
    print "generating action\n"
    python_action_code:extract the code from {result} between the first ```python and ```
    save python_action_code to ./final_action.py
    print "running action...\n"
    run cli: python3.11 final_action.py with output streaming
  }
}
